   =20
                  <h1 class=3D"title topictitle1" id=3D"ariaid-title1">Migr=
ate Your Management Center from the Source Model to the Target Model</h1>
                  <section class=3D"body">
                    =20
                     <p class=3D"p">This chapter provides information about=
 the prerequisites and the workflow for the management center model migrati=
on.</p>
                    =20
                  </section>
                  <!-- minitoc start -->
                  <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links">
                     <ul class=3D"ullinks">
                        <li class=3D"link ulchildlink"><a href=3D"https://w=
ww.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/fmc_model_migration/b_FMC_M=
odel_Migration_Guide/m_fmc_migration_workflow.html#id_111621">Prepare for M=
igration</a></li>
                        <li class=3D"link ulchildlink"><a href=3D"https://w=
ww.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/fmc_model_migration/b_FMC_M=
odel_Migration_Guide/m_fmc_migration_workflow.html#id_111624">Standalone Ma=
nagement Center Model Migration Workflow</a></li>
                        <li class=3D"link ulchildlink"><a href=3D"https://w=
ww.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/fmc_model_migration/b_FMC_M=
odel_Migration_Guide/m_fmc_migration_workflow.html#id_112763">Management Ce=
nter High-Availability Model Migration Workflow</a></li>
                        <li class=3D"link ulchildlink"><a href=3D"https://w=
ww.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/fmc_model_migration/b_FMC_M=
odel_Migration_Guide/m_fmc_migration_workflow.html#id_111629">How to Use th=
e Management Center Model Migration Script</a></li>
                        <li class=3D"link ulchildlink"><a href=3D"https://w=
ww.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/fmc_model_migration/b_FMC_M=
odel_Migration_Guide/m_fmc_migration_workflow.html#error-messages">Troubles=
hooting Management Center Model Migration</a></li>
                     </ul>
                  </nav>
                  <!-- minitoc end -->
                  <article class=3D"topic concept nested1" aria-labelledby=
=3D"ariaid-title2" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"id_111621">
                     <h2 class=3D"title topictitle2" id=3D"ariaid-title2">P=
repare for Migration</h2>
                     <section class=3D"body conbody">
                       =20
                        <section class=3D"section" id=3D"id_111621__d2790e6=
2">
                           <h3 class=3D"title sectiontitle">General Prerequ=
isites</h3>
                          =20
                          =20
                           <ul class=3D"ul" id=3D"id_111621__ul_k5l_yyr_13b=
">
                             =20
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">See <a class=3D"xref" href=
=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/fmc_model_migr=
ation/b_FMC_Model_Migration_Guide/about_fmc_model_migration.html#id_111597"=
>Supported Migration Paths</a> to determine which target model you can migr=
ate to from your source model.
                                 </p>
                                =20
                              </li>
                             =20
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">Management center model mig=
ration supports all management center licensing modes, including evaluation=
, connected, and Specific
                                    License Reservation (SLR).
                                 </p>
                                =20
                              </li>
                             =20
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">Ensure that the target mana=
gement center has the same number of interfaces as your source management c=
enter.</p>
                                =20
                              </li>
                             =20
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">Verify that the target mana=
gement center version matches the source management center version (includi=
ng patch,Vulnerability
                                    Database [VDB], Lightweight Security Pa=
ckage [LSP], and Snort Rule Update [SRU]). To verify, in each management ce=
nter choose
                                    <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Help</span=
> &gt; <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">About</span>.
                                 </p>
                                =20
                              </li>
                             =20
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">Verify that all the pending=
 deployments are completed successfully. </p>
                                =20
                              </li>
                             =20
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">Configure the backup file i=
n the source management center:</p>
                                =20
                                 <ol class=3D"ol">
                                   =20
                                    <li class=3D"li">
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">Choose <span class=3D=
"ph"><span class=3D"ph uicontrol">System</span><span class=3D"ph"> (<a href=
=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/dam/en/us/td/i/400001-500000/450001-460000/4510=
01-452000/451292.jpg" class=3D"show-image-alone" title=3D"system gear icon"=
><img class=3D"image" src=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/dam/en/us/td/i/400001-=
500000/450001-460000/451001-452000/451292.jpg" alt=3D"system gear icon"></a=
>)</span></span> &gt; <span class=3D"ph uicontrol">Backup/Restore</span>.=
=20
                                       </p>
                                      =20
                                    </li>
                                   =20
                                    <li class=3D"li">
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">Click the <span class=
=3D"ph uicontrol">Backup Mangement</span> tab and click <span class=3D"ph u=
icontrol">Firewall Mangement Backup</span>.
                                       </p>
                                      =20
                                    </li>
                                   =20
                                    <li class=3D"li">
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">Check the following c=
heck boxes:</p>
                                      =20
                                       <ul class=3D"ul">
                                         =20
                                          <li class=3D"li">
                                            =20
                                             <p class=3D"p"><span class=3D"=
ph uicontrol">Back Up Configuration</span></p>
                                            =20
                                          </li>
                                         =20
                                          <li class=3D"li">
                                            =20
                                             <p class=3D"p"><span class=3D"=
ph uicontrol">Backup Events</span></p>
                                            =20
                                          </li>
                                         =20
                                          <li class=3D"li">
                                            =20
                                             <p class=3D"p"><span class=3D"=
ph uicontrol">Backup Threat Intelligence Director</span></p>
                                            =20
                                          </li>
                                         =20
                                       </ul>
                                      =20
                                    </li>
                                   =20
                                 </ol>
                                =20
                              </li>
                             =20
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">Confirm that you have the c=
orrect number of threat defense entitlements in Cisco Smart Software Manage=
r (CSSM).</p>
                                =20
                              </li>
                             =20
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">If a management center migr=
ates to a higher platform and manages more threat defense devices, you must=
 acquire the required
                                    licenses for the additional threat defe=
nse devices.
                                 </p>
                                =20
                              </li>
                             =20
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">If the source management ce=
nter is Unified Capabilities Approved Products List (UCAPL) compliant or Co=
mmon Criteria (CC) compliant,
                                    after migration, the target management =
center will also be UCAPL or CC compliant.
                                 </p>
                                =20
                              </li>
                             =20
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">For management center HA mi=
grations:</p>
                                =20
                                 <ul class=3D"ul">
                                   =20
                                    <li class=3D"li">
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">If the target managem=
ent centers are in HA, you must pause the synchronization in the target man=
agement centers before the
                                          migration.
                                       </p>
                                      =20
                                    </li>
                                   =20
                                    <li class=3D"li">
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">Ensure that you meet =
all the HA requirements. For more information, see:</p>
                                      =20
                                       <ul class=3D"ul">
                                         =20
                                          <li class=3D"li">
                                            =20
                                             <p class=3D"p">For versions 6.=
5 to 7.1, see the Requirements for Firepower Management Center High Availab=
ility topic in the <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/=
support/security/defense-center/products-installation-and-configuration-gui=
des-list.html" target=3D"_blank"><cite class=3D"cite">Firepower Management =
Center Configuration Guide</cite></a>.
                                             </p>
                                            =20
                                          </li>
                                         =20
                                          <li class=3D"li">
                                            =20
                                             <p class=3D"p">For Version 7.2=
 and later, see the Requirements for Management Center High Availability to=
pic in the <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/support/=
security/defense-center/products-installation-and-configuration-guides-list=
.html" target=3D"_blank"><cite class=3D"cite">Cisco Secure Firewall Managem=
ent Center Administration Guide</cite></a>.
                                             </p>
                                            =20
                                          </li>
                                         =20
                                       </ul>
                                      =20
                                    </li>
                                   =20
                                 </ul>
                                =20
                              </li>
                             =20
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">After migration, you must d=
eregister the licenses from the source management center and register the l=
icenses in the target
                                    management center.
                                 </p>
                                =20
                              </li>
                             =20
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">After migration, if you wan=
t to manage a different group of threat defense devices in the source manag=
ement center:</p>
                                =20
                                 <ul class=3D"ul">
                                   =20
                                    <li class=3D"li">
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">Ensure that source ma=
nagement center cannot reach the stale threat defense devices.</p>
                                      =20
                                    </li>
                                   =20
                                    <li class=3D"li">
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">Delete the stale devi=
ces that are now managed by the target management center.</p>
                                      =20
                                    </li>
                                   =20
                                 </ul>
                                =20
                                 <table class=3D"olh_note" border=3D"0" rol=
e=3D"note">
                                    <tbody><tr>
                                       <td width=3D"1%" class=3D"olh_note" =
role=3D"heading" border=3D"0"><img src=3D"https://www.cisco.com/content/dam=
/en/us/td/i/templates/note.gif"><br><p><b>Note</b></p>
                                       </td>
                                       <td border=3D"0" class=3D"olh_note">
                                          <section class=3D"note__content">
                                             <hr>
                                            =20
                                             <p class=3D"p">If the source m=
anagement center can reach the stale devices, these devices will be deregis=
tered from the target management
                                                center.
                                             </p>
                                            =20
                                             <hr>
                                          </section>
                                       </td>
                                    </tr>
                                 </tbody></table>
                                =20
                              </li>
                             =20
                           </ul>
                          =20
                        </section>
                       =20
                        <section class=3D"section" id=3D"id_111621__d2790e2=
82">
                           <h3 class=3D"title sectiontitle">Prerequisites f=
or Migrating Management Center 1000, 2500, or 4500 to Management Center 170=
0, 2700, or 4700</h3>
                          =20
                          =20
                           <ol class=3D"ol">
                             =20
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">Ensure that Management Cent=
er 1000, 2500, or 4500 and all the corresponding managed threat defense dev=
ices are Version 7.0.x.
                                   =20
                                 </p>
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">We recommend that you use V=
ersion 7.0.5.</p>
                                =20
                              </li>
                             =20
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">Upgrade Management Center 1=
000, 2500, or 4500 from Version 7.0.x to 7.4.x. This upgrade is only for mi=
gration. </p>
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">You can download the upgrad=
e package from here: <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://software.cisco.com/d=
ownload/specialrelease/46aa635d7e042d9e794e36f28fad0877" target=3D"_blank">=
Special Release</a>. Unzip (but do not untar) the upgrade package before up=
loading it to the on-prem management center.
                                 </p>
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p"> For more information about=
 the upgrade, see the <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/=
us/td/docs/security/firepower/upgrade/fpmc-upgrade-guide.html" target=3D"_b=
lank"><cite class=3D"cite">Cisco Firepower Management Center Upgrade Guide,=
 Version 6.0=E2=80=937.0</cite></a></p>
                                =20
                              </li>
                             =20
                           </ol>
                          =20
                        </section>
                       =20
                        <section class=3D"section" id=3D"id_111621__d2790e3=
20">
                           <h3 class=3D"title sectiontitle">Prerequisites f=
or Management Center 1600, 2600, or 4600 to Management Center 1700, 2700, o=
r 4700</h3>
                          =20
                          =20
                           <ul class=3D"ul">
                             =20
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">Upgrade Management Center 1=
600, 2600, or 4600 to 7.4.x. For more information about upgrade, see <a cla=
ss=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/support/security/defense-=
center/products-installation-guides-list.html" target=3D"_blank"><cite clas=
s=3D"cite">Cisco Secure Firewall Threat Defense Upgrade Guide for Managemen=
t Center</cite></a>.=20
                                 </p>
                                =20
                              </li>
                             =20
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">Ensure that the source mana=
gement center manages only threat defense devices with Version 7.0.x. </p>
                                =20
                              </li>
                             =20
                           </ul>
                          =20
                        </section>
                       =20
                        <section class=3D"section" id=3D"id_111621__d2790e3=
46">
                           <h3 class=3D"title sectiontitle">Prerequisites f=
or Migrating Management Center 4600 to Management Center Virtual 300 (FMCv3=
00) for AWS</h3>
                          =20
                          =20
                           <ul class=3D"ul">
                             =20
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">Note that Management Center=
 Virtual 300 has lower limits than Management Center 4600. We recommend tha=
t you refer to the following

eck for Migrating Management Center 4600 to Management Center Virtual 300 f=

igration, you must update the following parameters:</p>

ter IP Address or Hostname on the Threat Defense Device</a>.

                        <section class=3D"section" id=3D"id_111621__d2790e5=
25">
                           <h3 class=3D"title sectiontitle">Limitations for=
 Migrating Management Center 1000/2500/4500/1600/2600/4600 to Management Ce=
nter 1700/2700/4700</h3>
                          =20
                          =20
                           <ul class=3D"ul">
                             =20
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">For the migration, you can =
upgrade Management Center 1000, 2500, or 4500 only from Version 7.0.x to 7.=
4.x. Upgrades from 7.0.x
                                    to 7.1.x, 7.2.x, or 7.3.x are not avail=
able.
                                 </p>
                                =20
                              </li>
                             =20
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">You cannot use Management C=
enter 1000, 2500, or 4500 with Version 7.4.x to manage threat defense devic=
es. Upgrades from 7.0.x
                                    to 7.4.x support only migration to Mana=
gement Center 1700, 2700, or 4700.=20
                                 </p>
                                =20
                              </li>
                             =20
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">You cannot migrate Manageme=
nt Center 1000, 2500, 4500, 1600, 2600, or 4600 that manage the following t=
ypes of devices:</p>
                                =20
                                 <ul class=3D"ul">
                                   =20
                                    <li class=3D"li">
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">Any threat defense de=
vice earlier than Version 7.0.x.</p>
                                      =20
                                    </li>
                                   =20
                                    <li class=3D"li">
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">NGIPSv or FirePOWER s=
ervices.</p>
                                      =20
                                    </li>
                                   =20
                                 </ul>
                                =20
                              </li>
                             =20
                           </ul>
                          =20
                        </section>
                     </section>

>Firepower Management Center Configuration Guide</cite></a>.=20
                                       </p>
                                      =20

ater, see the Back Up the Management Center topic in the <a class=3D"xref" =

agement center. If required,

agement center IP address after migration, you must do the following: </p>

te-the-fmc-ip-address-or-hostname-on-the-ftd">Update the Management Center =
IP Address or Hostname on the Threat Defense Device</a>.

configuration between the management center and its managed devices. </p>

anagement Center High-Availability Model Migration Workflow</h2>
                     <section class=3D"body conbody">
                       =20
                        <p class=3D"p">You can migrate your management cent=
er HA setup by executing the migration script on the target primary managem=
ent center
                           and secondary management center.
                        </p>

                        <p class=3D"p">The following flowchart illustrates =
the workflow for migrating your management center HA setup from the source =
models to the
                           target models.

ote" border=3D"0" role=3D"note">

eading" border=3D"0"><img src=3D"https://www.cisco.com/content/dam/en/us/td=
/i/templates/note.gif"><br><p><b>Note</b></p>
                              </td>

                                 <section class=3D"note__content">
                                    <hr>
                                   =20
                                    <p class=3D"p">Ensure that you meet the=
 prerequisites described in <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com=
/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/fmc_model_migration/b_FMC_Model_Migrati=
on_Guide/m_fmc_migration_workflow.html#id_111621">Prepare for Migration</a>=
.
                                    </p>
                                   =20
                                    <hr>
                                 </section>
                              </td>

eaders=3D"id_112763__table_ct1_cbs_13b__entry__2 ">
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">Verify that the HA co=
nfiguration of the management centers is healthy and that there are no aler=
ts.</p>

eaders=3D"id_112763__table_ct1_cbs_13b__entry__3 " colspan=3D"2">

.1, see the Viewing Firepower Management Center High Availability Status to=
pic in the <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/support/=
security/defense-center/products-installation-and-configuration-guides-list=
.html" target=3D"_blank"><cite class=3D"cite">Firepower Management Center C=
onfiguration Guide</cite></a>.
                                       </p>
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">For Version 7.2 and l=
ater, see the Viewing Management Center High Availability Status topic in t=
he <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/support/security=
/defense-center/products-installation-and-configuration-guides-list.html" t=
arget=3D"_blank"><cite class=3D"cite">Cisco Secure Firewall Management Cent=
er Administration Guide</cite></a>.
                                       </p>
                                      =20

                                    <td class=3D"entry colsep-1 rowsep-1" h=
eaders=3D"id_112763__table_ct1_cbs_13b__entry__1 ">
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p"><a href=3D"https://ww=
w.cisco.com/c/dam/en/us/td/i/400001-500000/430001-440000/439001-440000/4397=
52.jpg" class=3D"show-image-alone" title=3D"Related image, diagram or scree=
nshot."><img class=3D"image" src=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/dam/en/us/td/i/=
400001-500000/430001-440000/439001-440000/439752.jpg" width=3D"24"></a></p>
                                      =20
                                    </td>
                                   =20
                                    <td class=3D"entry colsep-1 rowsep-1" h=
eaders=3D"id_112763__table_ct1_cbs_13b__entry__2 ">
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">Register smart licens=
ing in the target primary active management center.</p>
                                      =20
                                    </td>
                                   =20
                                    <td class=3D"entry colsep-1 rowsep-1" h=
eaders=3D"id_112763__table_ct1_cbs_13b__entry__3 " colspan=3D"2">
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">For versions 6.5 to 7=
.1, see the License Requirements for Firepower Management Center topic in t=
he <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/support/security=
/defense-center/products-installation-and-configuration-guides-list.html" t=
arget=3D"_blank">Firepower Management Center Configuration Guide</a>.
                                       </p>
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">For Version 7.2 and l=
ater, see the Configure Smart Licensing topic in the <a class=3D"xref" href=
=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/support/security/defense-center/products-=
installation-and-configuration-guides-list.html" target=3D"_blank"><cite cl=
ass=3D"cite">Cisco Secure Firewall Management Center Administration Guide</=
cite></a>.
                                       </p>
                                      =20
                                    </td>

                                 </tr>

                                    <td class=3D"entry colsep-1 rowsep-1" h=
eaders=3D"id_112763__table_ct1_cbs_13b__entry__1 ">
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p"><a href=3D"https://ww=
w.cisco.com/c/dam/en/us/td/i/400001-500000/430001-440000/439001-440000/4397=
53.jpg" class=3D"show-image-alone" title=3D"Related image, diagram or scree=
nshot."><img class=3D"image" src=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/dam/en/us/td/i/=
400001-500000/430001-440000/439001-440000/439753.jpg" width=3D"24"></a></p>
                                      =20
                                    </td>
                                   =20
                                    <td class=3D"entry colsep-1 rowsep-1" h=
eaders=3D"id_112763__table_ct1_cbs_13b__entry__2 ">

                                       <p class=3D"p">Verify the heartbeats=
 for all the threat defense devices managed by the target management center=

eaders=3D"id_112763__table_ct1_cbs_13b__entry__3 " colspan=3D"2">

management center. Verify that all the configurations are restored and basi=

                  <article class=3D"topic task nested1 no_summary_steps" ar=
ia-labelledby=3D"ariaid-title5" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"id_111629">
                     <h2 class=3D"title topictitle2" id=3D"ariaid-title5">H=
ow to Use the Management Center Model Migration Script</h2>
                     <section class=3D"body taskbody">
                        <section class=3D"section context" id=3D"id_111629_=
_d2790e1530">
                          =20
                           <p class=3D"p">Perform the following procedure t=
o use the migration script. Note that this procedure is only one part of th=
e management center
                              model migration. See <a class=3D"xref" href=
=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/fmc_model_migr=
ation/b_FMC_Model_Migration_Guide/m_fmc_migration_workflow.html#id_111624">=
Standalone Management Center Model Migration Workflow</a> or <a class=3D"xr=
ef" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/fmc_mo=
del_migration/b_FMC_Model_Migration_Guide/m_fmc_migration_workflow.html#id_=
112763">Management Center High-Availability Model Migration Workflow</a> fo=
r details about the full model migration workflow.
                           </p>
                          =20
                        </section>
                        <section class=3D"tasklabel">
                           <h3 font-weight=3D"bold" class=3D"sectiontitle t=
asklabel cB_Bold">Procedure</h3>
                        </section>
                        <hr noshade=3D"">
                        <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table class=3D"stepT=
able" border=3D"0">
                           <tbody>
                              <tr class=3D"li step">
                                 <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" border=
=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                    <p><b>Step&nbsp;1</b></p>
                                 </td>
                                 <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" border=
=3D"0">
                                    <p class=3D"ph cmd">Log in to the targe=
t management center CLI.  </p>
                                 </td>
                              </tr>
                             =20
                              <tr class=3D"li step">
                                 <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" border=
=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                    <p><b>Step&nbsp;2</b></p>
                                 </td>
                                 <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" border=
=3D"0">
                                    <p class=3D"ph cmd">Run the <span class=
=3D"keyword cmdname">expert</span> command to switch to expert mode.
                                    </p>
                                 </td>
                              </tr>
                              <tr class=3D"li step">
                                 <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" border=
=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                    <p><b>Step&nbsp;3</b></p>
                                 </td>
                                 <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" border=
=3D"0">
                                    <p class=3D"ph cmd">Execute the migrati=
on command:</p>
                                    <section class=3D"itemgroup info">
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p"><span><span class=3D"=
keyword kwd">/var/sf/backup/sf-migration.pl</span>
                                             <var>backup_file_path</var> </=
span></p>
                                      =20
                                    </section>
                                    <section class=3D"itemgroup stepxmp">
                                       <section class=3D"tasklabel">
                                          <h3 font-weight=3D"bold" class=3D=
"sectiontitle tasklabel cB_Bold">Example:</h3>
                                       </section>
                                      =20
                                       <section class=3D"p">
                                          <pre class=3D"pre codeblock"><cod=
e>
root@firepower:# /var/sf/bin/sf-migration.pl /var/sf/backup/100localbackup-=
2023-05-20examp.tar</code></pre>
                                          </section>
                                      =20
                                    </section>
                                    <section class=3D"itemgroup info">
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">Note that when the mi=
gration process is completed, the system reboots.</p>
                                      =20
                                    </section>
                                 </td>
                              </tr>
                           </tbody>
                        </table></div>
                        <hr noshade=3D"">
                        <section class=3D"section postreq" id=3D"id_111629_=
_d2790e1584">
                           <section class=3D"tasklabel">
                              <h3 font-weight=3D"bold" class=3D"sectiontitl=
e tasklabel cB_Bold">What to do next</h3>
                           </section>
                          =20
                           <p class=3D"p">Return to <a class=3D"xref" href=
=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/fmc_model_migr=
ation/b_FMC_Model_Migration_Guide/m_fmc_migration_workflow.html#id_111624">=
Standalone Management Center Model Migration Workflow</a> or <a class=3D"xr=
ef" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/fmc_mo=
del_migration/b_FMC_Model_Migration_Guide/m_fmc_migration_workflow.html#id_=
112763">Management Center High-Availability Model Migration Workflow</a> an=
d complete all the remaining steps.
                           </p>
                          =20
                        </section>
                     </section>
                     <!-- minitoc start -->
                     <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links">
                        <ul class=3D"ullinks">
                           <li class=3D"link ulchildlink"><a href=3D"https:=
//www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/fmc_model_migration/b_FM=
C_Model_Migration_Guide/m_fmc_migration_workflow.html#update-the-fmc-ip-add=
ress-or-hostname-on-the-ftd">Update the Management Center IP Address or Hos=
tname on the Threat Defense Device</a></li>
                        </ul>
                     </nav>
                     <!-- minitoc end -->
                     <article class=3D"topic task nested2 no_summary_steps"=
 aria-labelledby=3D"ariaid-title6" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"update-the-fmc-ip-a=
ddress-or-hostname-on-the-ftd">
                        <h3 class=3D"title topictitle3" id=3D"ariaid-title6=
">Update the Management Center IP Address or Hostname on the Threat Defense=
 Device</h3>
                        <section class=3D"body taskbody">
                           <section class=3D"section context" id=3D"update-=
the-fmc-ip-address-or-hostname-on-the-ftd__d2790e1626">
                             =20
                              <p class=3D"p">After migration, if the networ=
k configuration of the target management center is different from that of t=
he source management
                                 center, you must update the IP address or =
hostname of the management center on each threat defense device.=20
                              </p>
                             =20
                           </section>
                           <section class=3D"tasklabel">
                              <h4 font-weight=3D"bold" class=3D"sectiontitl=
e tasklabel cB_Bold">Procedure</h4>
                           </section>
                           <hr noshade=3D"">
                           <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table class=3D"st=
epTable" border=3D"0">
                              <tbody>
                                =20
                                 <tr class=3D"li step">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;1</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">From the threat =
defense CLI, get the unique identifier for the management center using the =
<span class=3D"keyword cmdname">show managers</span> command:
                                       </p>
                                       <section class=3D"itemgroup stepxmp"=
>
                                          <section class=3D"tasklabel">
                                             <h4 font-weight=3D"bold" class=
=3D"sectiontitle tasklabel cB_Bold">Example:</h4>
                                          </section>
                                          <pre class=3D"pre codeblock"><cod=
e>&gt; show managers
Type                      : Manager
Host                      : xx.xx.x.x
Display name              : xx.xx.x.x
Identifier                : f7ffad78-bf16-11ec-a737-baa2f76ef602
Registration              : Completed
Management type           : Configuration and analytics
 </code></pre>
                                          </section>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                =20
                                 <tr class=3D"li step">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;2</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">Update the manag=
ement center IP address or hostname using the <span class=3D"keyword cmdnam=
e">configure manager</span> command:
                                       </p>
                                       <section class=3D"itemgroup info">
                                         =20
                                          <p class=3D"p"><span><span class=
=3D"keyword kwd">configure manager edit </span><var>fmc_uuid </var><span cl=
ass=3D"keyword kwd">hostname </span><var>fmc_ipaddress</var> </span>
                                            =20
                                          </p>
                                         =20
                                       </section>
                                       <section class=3D"itemgroup stepxmp"=
>
                                          <section class=3D"tasklabel">
                                             <h4 font-weight=3D"bold" class=
=3D"sectiontitle tasklabel cB_Bold">Example:</h4>
                                          </section>
                                          <pre class=3D"pre codeblock"><cod=
e>&gt; configure manager edit f7ffad78-bf16-11ec-a737-baa2f76ef602 hostname=
 xx.xx.x.x
Updating hostname from xx.xx.x.x to xx.xx.x.x
Manager hostname updated.
</code></pre>
                                          </section>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                =20
                                 <tr class=3D"li step">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;3</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">Update the manag=
ement center display name using the <span class=3D"keyword cmdname">configu=
re manager</span> command:
                                       </p>
                                       <section class=3D"itemgroup info">
                                         =20
                                          <p class=3D"p"><span><span class=
=3D"keyword kwd">configure manager edit </span><var>fmc_uuid </var><span cl=
ass=3D"keyword kwd">displayname </span><var>fmc_ipaddress</var> </span>
                                            =20
                                          </p>
                                         =20
                                       </section>
                                       <section class=3D"itemgroup stepxmp"=
>
                                          <section class=3D"tasklabel">
                                             <h4 font-weight=3D"bold" class=
=3D"sectiontitle tasklabel cB_Bold">Example:</h4>
                                          </section>
                                          <pre class=3D"pre codeblock"><cod=
e>&gt; configure manager edit f7ffad78-bf16-11ec-a737-baa2f76ef602 displayn=
ame xx.xx.x.x
Updating displayname from xx.xx.x.x to xx.xx.x.x
Manager displayname updated.
</code></pre>
                                          </section>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                =20
                                 <tr class=3D"li step">
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0" width=3D"10%">
                                       <p><b>Step&nbsp;4</b></p>
                                    </td>
                                    <td align=3D"left" valign=3D"top" borde=
r=3D"0">
                                       <p class=3D"ph cmd">Verify the updat=
ed management center configuration using the <span class=3D"keyword cmdname=
">show managers</span> command again.
                                       </p>
                                    </td>
                                 </tr>
                                =20
                              </tbody>
                           </table></div>
                           <hr noshade=3D"">
                        </section>
                        <!-- minitoc start -->
                        <nav role=3D"navigation" class=3D"related-links"></=
nav>
                        <!-- minitoc end -->
                     </article>
                  </article>
                  <article class=3D"topic reference nested1" aria-labelledb=
y=3D"ariaid-title7" lang=3D"en-US" id=3D"error-messages">
                     <h2 class=3D"title topictitle2" id=3D"ariaid-title7">T=
roubleshooting Management Center Model Migration</h2>
                     <section class=3D"body refbody">
                       =20
                        <section class=3D"section" id=3D"error-messages__d2=
790e1749">
                          =20
                           <div class=3D"tableContainer"><table width=3D"10=
0%" border=3D"1" class=3D"table frame-all">
                              <caption><span class=3D"table--title-label ta=
bletitle">Table 4. </span><span class=3D"tabletitle">Management Center Mode=
l Migration Error Messages</span></caption>

                              </colgroup>
                              <thead class=3D"thead">

                                 <tr>
                                   =20
                                    <th font-weight=3D"bold" class=3D"entry=
 colsep-1 rowsep-1" id=3D"error-messages__entry__1">

                                       <p class=3D"p">Error Message</p>
                                      =20
                                    </th>

 colsep-1 rowsep-1" id=3D"error-messages__entry__2">

                                       <p class=3D"p">Recommended Action</p=
>
                                      =20
                                    </th>

                                 </tr>

                              <tbody class=3D"tbody">
                                =20
                                 <tr>
                                   =20
                                    <td class=3D"entry colsep-1 rowsep-1" h=
eaders=3D"error-messages__entry__1 ">
                                      =20
                                       <section class=3D"p">
                                          <pre class=3D"pre codeblock"><cod=

eaders=3D"error-messages__entry__2 ">

                                       <p class=3D"p">Increase the size of =

                                =20
                                 <tr>
                                   =20
                                    <td class=3D"entry colsep-1 rowsep-1" h=
eaders=3D"error-messages__entry__1 ">
                                      =20
                                       <section class=3D"p">
                                          <pre class=3D"pre codeblock"><cod=
e>Interface count mismatch.</code></pre>
                                          </section>
                                      =20
                                    </td>
                                   =20
                                    <td class=3D"entry colsep-1 rowsep-1" h=
eaders=3D"error-messages__entry__2 ">
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">The source and target=
 management centers must have the same number of interfaces. See <a class=
=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/=
fmc_model_migration/b_FMC_Model_Migration_Guide/m_fmc_migration_workflow.ht=
ml#id_111621">Prepare for Migration</a>.
                                       </p>
                                      =20
                                    </td>
                                   =20
                                 </tr>
                                =20
                                 <tr>
                                   =20
                                    <td class=3D"entry colsep-1 rowsep-1" h=
eaders=3D"error-messages__entry__1 ">
                                      =20
                                       <section class=3D"p">
                                          <pre class=3D"pre codeblock"><cod=
e>No migration path exists from the=20
Secure Firewall Management Center 4500 to=20
Secure Firewall Management Center 2700.</code></pre>
                                          </section>
                                      =20
                                    </td>
                                   =20
                                    <td class=3D"entry colsep-1 rowsep-1" h=
eaders=3D"error-messages__entry__2 ">
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p"> See <a class=3D"xref=
" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/fmc_mode=

11597">Supported Migration Paths</a>.

eaders=3D"error-messages__entry__1 ">

                                       <section class=3D"p">

e>No migration path exists from the=20
Secure Firewall Management Center 4600 to the=20
Secure Firewall Management Center for VMware 300.</code></pre>
                                          </section>
                                      =20
                                    </td>
                                   =20
                                    <td class=3D"entry colsep-1 rowsep-1" h=
eaders=3D"error-messages__entry__2 " rowspan=3D"2">
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">You can migrate a Sec=
ure Firewall Management Center 4600 to only a Management Center Virtual 300=
 (FMCv300) for AWS<span class=3D"ph"> or Secure Firewall Management Center =
4700</span>. See <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td=
/docs/security/firepower/fmc_model_migration/b_FMC_Model_Migration_Guide/ab=
out_fmc_model_migration.html#id_111597">Supported Migration Paths</a>.

                                      =20

                                   =20
                                 </tr>
                                =20
                                 <tr>

                                    <td class=3D"entry colsep-1 rowsep-1" h=
eaders=3D"error-messages__entry__1 ">
                                      =20
                                       <section class=3D"p">
                                          <pre class=3D"pre codeblock"><cod=
e>No migration path exists from the=20
Secure Firewall Management Center&nbsp;4600 to=20
Secure Firewall Management Center for Azure 300.</code></pre>
                                          </section>
                                      =20
                                    </td>
                                   =20
                                 </tr>
                                =20
                                 <tr>
                                   =20
                                    <td class=3D"entry colsep-1 rowsep-1" h=
eaders=3D"error-messages__entry__1 ">
                                      =20
                                       <section class=3D"p">
                                          <pre class=3D"pre codeblock"><cod=
e>Device count is more than 300.</code></pre>

                                    </td>
                                   =20
                                    <td class=3D"entry colsep-1 rowsep-1" h=
eaders=3D"error-messages__entry__2 ">
                                      =20
                                       <ol class=3D"ol">
                                         =20
                                          <li class=3D"li">
                                            =20
                                             <p class=3D"p">Reduce the devi=
ce count in the source management center (Secure Firewall Management Center=
 4600). </p>
                                            =20
                                          </li>
                                         =20
                                          <li class=3D"li">
                                            =20
                                             <p class=3D"p">Create a backup=
 file in the source management center before migrating to the target manage=
ment center (Management Center Virtual
                                                300 [FMCv300] for AWS).=20
                                             </p>
                                            =20
                                          </li>
                                         =20
                                       </ol>
                                      =20
                                       <p class=3D"p">See <a class=3D"xref"=
 href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/security/firepower/fmc_model=
_migration/b_FMC_Model_Migration_Guide/m_fmc_migration_workflow.html#id_111=
621">Prepare for Migration</a>.

                        <section class=3D"section" id=3D"error-messages__d2=
790e1923">
                           <h3 class=3D"title sectiontitle">Model Migration=
 of Management Center 1000/2500/4500 or 1600/2600/4600 to Management Center=
 1700/2700/4700</h3>
                          =20
                          =20
                          =20
                           <p class=3D"p">For model migration of management=
 center 1000/2500/4500 or 1600/2600/4600 to management center 1700/2700/470=
0:</p>
                          =20
                           <p class=3D"p">If the migration does not functio=
n to your expectations and you want to switch back, note that Version 7.4 i=
s unsupported
                              for general operations on the 1000/2500/4500 =
and 1600/2600/4600 devices. To return the old management center to a suppor=
ted
                              version, you must reimage back to Version 7.0=
.x, and restore from backup.
                           </p>
                          =20
                           <p class=3D"p">For more information about reimag=
ing the management center to Version 7.0.x, see the Getting Started Guide f=
or your management
                              center:
                           </p>
                          =20
                           <ul class=3D"ul">
                             =20
                              <li class=3D"li">
                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">For management center 1000/=
2500/4500, see <a class=3D"xref" href=3D"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/d=
ocs/security/firepower/hw/getting-started/fmc-1000-2500-4500/fmc-1000-2500-=
4500.html#id_80689" target=3D"_blank">Cisco Firepower Management Center 100=
0, 2500, and 4500 Getting Started Guide</a>.
                                 </p>
                                =20

                                =20
                                 <p class=3D"p">For management center 1600/=

ocs/security/firepower/hw/getting-started/fmc-1600-2600-4600/fmc-1600-2600-=
4600.html#id_80689" target=3D"_blank">Cisco Firepower Management Center 160=
0, 2600, and 4600 Getting Started Guide</a>.
                                 </p>
                                =20

  button { width: auto; }
}

idden; }

.arcade-mode .interstitial-wrapper { height: 100vh; max-width: 100%; overfl=
ow: hidden; }

.arcade-mode .runner-container { left: 0px; margin: auto; right: 0px; trans=
form-origin: center top; transition: transform 250ms cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 1=
, 1) 400ms; z-index: 2; }

@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {

  .offline .runner-canvas { filter: invert(1); }

vert(0); }
  .offline.inverted body { background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); }
  .offline.inverted .offline-runner-live-region { color: rgb(255, 255, 255)=
; }
  #suggestions-list a { color: var(--link-color); }
  #error-information-button { filter: invert(0.6); }

gle-gray-100); }
  .slow-speed-option .slow-speed-toggle::before, .slow-speed-option [type=
=3D"checkbox"]:checked:disabled + .slow-speed-toggle::before { background: =
rgb(189, 193, 198); }
  .slow-speed-option [type=3D"checkbox"]:checked + .slow-speed-toggle::afte=
r, .slow-speed-option [type=3D"checkbox"]:checked + .slow-speed-toggle::bef=
ore { background: var(--google-blue-300); }
}
